  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Effective Disaster Mitigation and Response in the North East Department of Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IMC is now in its second year in providing cholera case management in the 13 communes in the North East. The IMC MMU (Medical Mobile Units) are steeped in community relations, local government and in emergency interventions. It is currently working with ECHO funds until the 31 of October, 2015 The proposed work under ERRF involves training/WASH interventions, shelter management, with a gender equity component and critical disaster mitigation projects all of which impact the overall health situation in communities.  The OCHA ERFF DRR project complements the ECHO funded grant in the following ways; established community relations all of the 13 communes in the North East Department, coordination with all the actors working in the North East in health/WASH and DRR, and shared technical support by the staff already operational out the IMC Fort Libert&#xE9; office</narrative>
  </description>
